FBIS4-58173 "drnes084_k_94001" FBIS-NES-94-084 Daily Report 30 Apr 1994 IRAQ Saddam Husayn Visits al-Anbar Governorate Saddam Husayn Visits al-Anbar Governorate JN3004185194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 30 Apr 94 JN3004185194 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn today visited al-Anbar Governorate and met with several tribal chieftains in the presence of al-Anbar Governor Mani' 'Abd Rashid and the secretary and members of the al-Anbar branch of the Arab Socialist Ba'th Party. Speakers from the residents and tribal chieftains in al-Anbar Governorate reiterated their absolute love for and loyalty to the leadership of the leader president, may God preserve him, until total victory over the enemies is achieved, God willing. In speeches and poetry they delivered before the president, several chieftains voiced their great pride in the interest his excellency takes in the city of al-Ramadi and the rest of the governorate's cities, as well as his personal interest in the projects that are implemented. The leader president, may God preserve him, delivered an important speech in which he praised the position of the residents of al-Anbar Governorate, pointing out that it was historic, that future generations will remember it with pride, and that history will record the militant position and steadfastness of all the sons of great Iraq.
